{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/Ai3fiCnWzHl3bL4CZQQ1pt2uiOU.jpg","belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":35,"name":"Comedy"}],"homepage":"","id":5558,"imdb_id":"tt0071487","origin_country":["FR"],"original_language":"fr","original_title":"Le Fantôme de la liberté","overview":"This Surrealist film, with a title referencing the Communist Manifesto, strings together short incidents based on the life of director Luis Buñuel. Presented as chance encounters, these loosely related, intersecting situations, all without a consistent protagonist, reach from the 19th century to the 1970s. Touching briefly on subjects such as execution, pedophilia, incest, and sex, the film features an array of characters, including a sick father and incompetent police officers.","popularity":0.7887,"poster_path":"/f6cON5ebistPm6AS1XcZZMmKpIi.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":1657,"logo_path":null,"name":"Greenwich Film Production","origin_country":"FR"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"FR","name":"France"}],"release_date":"1974-09-10","revenue":6749,"runtime":104,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"French","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"Luis Bunuel's kinkiest comedy.","title":"The Phantom of Liberty","video":false,"vote_average":7.45,"vote_count":328,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[{"iso_3166_1":"CN","title":"自由的魅影","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","title":"자유의 환상","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","title":"El fantasma de la libertad","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"GR","title":"To fantasma tis eleftherias","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"GR","title":"Το φάντασμα της ελευθερίας","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"PT","title":"O Fantasma da Liberdade","type":""},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","title":"자유의 환영","type":""}]}}